<br>
- Pet will have trouble getting into ass/sup sometimes.<br>
<br>
- Never, ever, ever walk your pet across the bridge. He paths fine but it aggros all the frogs at the bottom.<br>
<br>
- Be very cautious at the bridge network near the evil eye. You can get the pet through without trouble if you just walk him carefully, but if you carelessly take off towards the live tower, your pet may decide to go through the jail and noble areas and meet you there with a lot of new friends.<br>
<br>
- Your pet will not usually cross a pit. This is especially important when going to magus (he'll go through the three mobs instead of jumping the pit in the other hall), or the pit trap outside of elder (not sure what the pet would do here.)<br>
<br>
- I'm pretty sure that your pet will not swim up to the hand. Admittedly, I've never tried it.<br>
<br>
- Your pet will not necessarily take the same route you do between safe hall and magus, and again between magus and lord. Just clear the hall and you won't have a problem.<br>
<br>
All of these trouble spots I consider to be acceptable pitfalls when dealing with a pet. You learn them early on and deal with them. Therefore I don't consider them &quot;bad pathing.&quot;<br>
<br>
I consider bad pathing to be what you get in The Hole when you're in a wide open area outside the castle but the pet takes a crazy zig zag path all over the place just because the mob you're fighting moved an inch or so.<br>
<br>
All zones either have pathing or they don't. Most outdoor zones have no pathing, so mobs walk through trees and such but at least they go in a straight line. Most indoor dungeons like Lower Guk have pathing to assist the mobs in navigating mazes (otherwise the mobs would walk through walls like they do outdoors.)<br>
<br>
I've noticed that &quot;bad pathing&quot; primarily occurs in dungeons that require pathing to navigate some areas, but also have large wide open areas that resemble outdoor zones. Since the dungeon needs to have pathing in the mazy parts, there's also pathing in the open parts... and that's when mobs start running all over the place. <br>
<br>
Think about the dungeons with historically bad pathing: Mistmoore, Cazic Thule, The Hole, Kerra Isle, City of Mist, etc. All these dungeons contain both mazy indoor and open outdoor areas. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz, "Gnome of Action"</b><br>Devout Agnostic Magician of the 54th Trial<i><br>Member of Silmindo, Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill>The Hunt</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM GAMES AD SCRIPT -->
